        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 2 at 8:12PM MDT until June 2 at 8:45PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>SVRBOU

The National Weather Service in Denver has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Morgan County in northeastern Colorado...
Northwestern Washington County in northeastern Colorado...

* Until 845 PM MDT.

* At 812 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Gary, or 17
miles southwest of Akron, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect
hail damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.
Expect wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Midway and Gary.
</description>
        <instruction>Anyone outdoors should move to shelter inside a well-built structure
and stay away from windows. This storm is capable of producing
dangerous hail and damaging winds.

Tornadoes can develop quickly from severe thunderstorms. Seek
shelter immediately in an interior room on the lowest floor of a
well-built structure.</instruction>
